# Cursor Rules â€” Project Guidelines

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **Package Manager**: npm

## Code Style
- Use functional components with TypeScript interfaces for props
- Prefer named exports over default exports for components
- File naming: `kebab-case` for files, `PascalCase` for components
- Use `@/` path alias for imports from `src/`
- Co-locate component styles with the component (Tailwind utility classes)

## Component Conventions
- All shared UI lives in `src/components/ui/`
- Page-specific components live in `src/components/` or the page folder
- Use `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils` for conditional class merging
- Keep components small and focused â€” split when > ~150 lines

## Tailwind Guidelines
- Prefer Tailwind utilities over custom CSS
- Use `@apply` sparingly â€” only in `globals.css` for truly global patterns
- Extend the theme in `tailwind.config.ts` rather than using arbitrary values
- Use semantic color names via CSS variables: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, etc.

## TypeScript
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; `type` for unions/primitives
- Avoid `any` â€” use `unknown` + type narrowing instead
- Always type function parameters and return types explicitly

## File Structure
```
src/
  app/          # Next.js App Router pages & layouts
  components/
    ui/         # Base design-system components
  hooks/        # Custom React hooks
  lib/          # Utilities and shared logic
  styles/       # Global CSS
```

## Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx`
- Hooks: `use-kebab-case.ts`
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts`
- Types/interfaces: `PascalCase`, suffix with `Props` for component props

## Design Knowledge
- Read `docs/DESIGN-CASE-STUDY-KNOWLEDGE.md` for design principles, case study context, and component prompting patterns derived from real product engagements (EQ Sight, BlackRock, Grabbi, SVB).
- When generating UI components, reference the relevant case study's "Cursor Prompting Tips" section for opinionated, context-aware guidance.
- Cross-project principles (speed, design systems, accessibility, measurable outcomes) apply to every component in this project.

## Design System Reference Knowledge
- **Portfolio UI** follows **ClickHouse** (`docs/design-md/clickhouse/DESIGN.md`): pure black canvas (`#000000`), **Neon Volt** (`#faff69`) accents & primary CTAs, **Forest Green** (`#166534`) secondary actions, charcoal borders `rgba(65,65,65,0.8)`, Inter weight 900 display / 600 UI, **4pxâ€“8px radius** (sharp geometry), Inconsolata for code, dark-only surfaces.
- For other branded prompts, use `docs/design-md/<company>/DESIGN.md` and `README.md`.

## Case study digital artifacts
- **Source folders (repo root)**: `case-study-images/<Folder>/` and `case-study-videos/<Folder>/` with human-readable folder names (`Energy Quotient`, `BlackRock`, `Grabbi`, `SVB`). Slugs in code map via `CASE_STUDY_ASSET_FOLDER` in `src/lib/case-study-media.ts`.
- **Served URLs**: `public/case-study-images/<slug>/` and `public/case-study-videos/<slug>/` are **symlinks** into those project folders so Next.js can serve them at `/case-study-images/...` and `/case-study-videos/...`. After clone or if links break, run `bash scripts/link-case-study-assets.sh` (or `npm run link-case-study-assets` if defined).
- **Code**: `getCaseStudyImages` / `getCaseStudyVideos` list files and emit URL-encoded paths for filenames with spaces.

## Git
- Commit messages: imperative mood (`Add`, `Fix`, `Update`)
- Branch names: `feature/`, `fix/`, `chore/`
